FBIS4-63904 "drsov102_b_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-102 Daily Report 25 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Yeltsin Signs Law Strengthening War on Crime Yeltsin Signs Law Strengthening War on Crime LD2505185094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1738 GMT 25 May 94 LD2505185094 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Shevtsov] [Text] Moscow May 25 -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin signed a decree today approving the federal programme for the strengthening of the struggle against crime for 1994-1995 which was earlier adopted by the security council. The implementation of this programme envisages consolidation of efforts by the law enforcement bodies, state institutions and society as a whole, a spokesman for the press service of the security council of the Russian Federation told ITAR-TASS on Wednesday. The document approved by the president provides for the unification of economic, political, legal, educational and organisational measures aimed at combining the interests of an individual citizen and society. The top priority direction in the struggle against crime is the establishment of corresponding legislative, and organisational and legal foundations, measures for the prevention of crime, and stopping crimes against life, health and property of citizens. Special attention is paid to checking malfeasance, economic and organised crime, and offenses in the armed forces of the Russian Federation.
